The incident occured in a courtroom, where a man who was just convicted of murder and robbery for killing a tourist from Oregon for his watch, jumped a Deputy Sherriff, and injured the Deputy before being shot dead by the Homicide Detective who was there as a wittness for the prosecution. When discussing this at work, I mentioned that while it was too bad that the Deputy got injured, it was good that the convicted murderer was killed. I mentioned that it was swift justice, and that it saved the taxpayers money that would have been spent putting this loser in jail, ony to have him released into Society in approx 15 years or so (or even less). A co-worker of mine thought that was a pretty bad thing to say, and thought that the detective should have shot him to injure. <br>
Personally, I think it would make a Hell of a lot of sense to fry some of these criminals who commit heinous crimes, and acts of violence, but there are those who feel that they should be allowed to live, and eventually be &quot;rehabilitated&quot; (yea right), and subsequently released back into Society. Personally, I feel that anyone that commits murder, rape, torture, terrorism, or child molestation should be executed.<br>
What are your thoughts on this? I'm curious to know.<br>
